<paragraph blockId="10.[199,1772,1392,2201]" pageId="10" pageNumber="36">
Male. Diminutive, dark coloured spider. Carapace oval, low, almost black with metallic shine. Colourless hairs cover carapace, white hairs form line along lateral edges and small patches behind posterior lateral eyes. Some dark bristles on eye ﬁeld. Mouthparts brown, only chewing margins of gnatocoxae light, sternum light brown. Abdomen ovoid, black with three pairs of white spots, anterior pair extends to streak on abdominal sides. Shiny scales cover abdomen. Venter blackish. Spinnerets black. Legs orange, femur of ﬁrst pair with brown lateral surfaces. Leg hairs and spines brown. Pedipalps dark brown. Palpal femur without apophyses, two apophyses on tibia, dorsal one short, spike-like (
<figureCitation box="[1382,1588,2017,2056]" captionStart="Figures 22 - 24. I" captionStartId="10.[200,311,1218,1260]" captionTargetBox="[199,1777,206,1168]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figures 22 - 24. I _ - leli 0 phani _ llııs metallifer nov. spec. 22: Palpal organ in ventral view; 23: Same in lateral view; 24: Same m dorsal View." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/305346/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="36">Figs 23, 24</figureCitation>
), tegulum irregular, embolus bent (
<figureCitation box="[613,729,2064,2103]" captionStart="Figures 22 - 24. I" captionStartId="10.[200,311,1218,1260]" captionTargetBox="[199,1777,206,1168]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figures 22 - 24. I _ - leli 0 phani _ llııs metallifer nov. spec. 22: Palpal organ in ventral view; 23: Same in lateral view; 24: Same m dorsal View." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/305346/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="36">
Fig. 
<number box="[690,729,2066,2094]" pageId="10" pageNumber="36" value="22.0">22</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
